I&#39;ve also noticed that people can get different feelings when their Blood Sugar is low.  And I&#39;ve been wondering if it would be possible to standardize a check of this B Sgr before doing much investigation or interpretation of evidence. In fact, it could be that the most  important tool in ghost hunter would be a B S detector.


--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, &quot;Tom&quot; &lt;Tom_Ray@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Dont forget thermometers to check for &quot;cold spots&quot;---Are the spots actually &quot;Cold&quot; or are they making us FEEL cold?
&gt; Also a compass for magnetic fluctuations.
&gt; Some of those ultrasonic or IR motion detectors (real cheap at radio shack)
&gt; A hygrometer for measuring dewpoint( at what temp water in air will condense to form a mist---great for correlating with cold spots---mist apparations)
&gt; A K2 meter--only 50 bucks or so.  great for &quot;gross screening&quot; of the area
&gt; A natural EM trifield meter  a bit expensive($200-250) but standard ghost hunting equipment.
